üí¨ Sample Answer (Conflict / Technical Discussion Example)

Situation:
In our hotel reservation project, we had to integrate multiple modules ‚Äî like booking, payment, and user management.
There was a bit of confusion in the team about which service communication approach we should use ‚Äî Feign Client, WebClient, or the traditional RestTemplate.

Task:
As I was working on the booking and payment integration, I needed clarity on which approach would work best for scalability and simplicity.

Action:
I compared all three options:

RestTemplate: Simple and blocking, but being deprecated.

WebClient: Reactive and non-blocking, good for scalability.

Feign Client: Declarative, integrates easily with Spring Cloud and works well for microservices.

I shared my findings with the team ‚Äî that since our services were microservice-based and using Spring Cloud, Feign Client would be the most suitable for internal service-to-service calls.

Result:
The team agreed, and we implemented Feign Client for inter-service communication. It simplified our code and improved maintainability.

Later, we used WebClient in the gateway for asynchronous calls, which gave us both simplicity and performance.

‚úÖ This answer highlights that you:

Can make technical comparisons.

Think about maintainability and scalability.
